<title>UK: Carlton squeezed higher by bargain-hunters.</title>
<headline>Carlton squeezed higher by bargain-hunters.</headline>
<dateline>LONDON 1997-03-26</dateline>
<text>
<p>Shares in Carlton Communications Plc were squeezed higher on Wednesday as bargain hunters sought to buy the stock after its recent decline, dealers said.</p>
<p>Shares in the media group were up 15-1/2p at 518-1/2 by 1213 GMT.</p>
<p>&quot;They've had a bad run recently and people are now looking at them as one of the stocks which is due a bounce,&quot; one market-maker said. &quot;It looks like they've been squeezed higher by that.&quot;</p>
<p>Carlton shares slid from 579p in early February to 497 on March 24.</p>
<p>-- Andrew Marshall, London newsroom +44 171 542 5106</p>
